15 (A) A temporary vacancy of the chairperson shall be filled by a majority vote of the
16 elected members of the board. All other temporary vacancies on the board shall be
17 filled by a majority vote of the elected members of the board after an application and
18 nomination process, as follows:
19 (i) The county clerk shall advertise on the county's public website and in the county
20 legal organ, once per week for a period of two weeks, the board's intention to fill the
21 vacancy, instructions for submitting an application to be nominated to fill the
22 vacancy, and deadlines for submitting such application. The county clerk shall
23 provide each elected member of the commission with a copy of each submitted
24 application;
25 (ii) At the next regular meeting or specially called meeting of the board after the
26 application deadline, the county clerk shall present the submitted applications to the
27 board and the board may accept additional nominations to fill the vacancy; and
28 (iii) At such meeting, a vote shall be taken by the elected members of the board to fill
29 the vacancy from the qualified applicants and nominees; and
30 (B) No person shall be elected pursuant to subparagraph (A) of this paragraph who:
31 (i) Does not meet the residency requirement for the vacant position as of the date of
32 submitting an application;
33 (ii) Has pending litigation against the county;
34 (iii) Has been convicted of a felony or has a pending indictment for a felony; or
35 (iv) Does not:
36 (I) Certify his or her political party or political body affiliation through his or her
37 respective political party or political body; or
38 (II) State in his or her application that he or she is unaffiliated with any political
39 party or political body.
40 (2) If the vacancy is a permanent vacancy:
