41 (A) In the event that the unexpired term of the vacant position is six months or less, the
42 chief judge of the Superior Court of Douglas County shall appoint a successor to serve
43 for the remainder of such term; or
44 (B) In the event that the unexpired term of the vacant position is more than six months,
45 the vacancy shall be filled at the next available special election date. Such special
46 election shall be called and held in the manner prescribed by Chapter 2 of Title 21 of
47 the O.C.G.A., the 'Georgia Election Code.'
48 (3) No person shall be appointed or elected to fill a vacancy who does not meet the
49 qualifications necessary to qualify for election as a commissioner.
50 (4) Persons elected or appointed to fill a vacancy shall take the same oath of office and
51 receive the same compensation as elected commissioners."
52 SECTION 2.
53 This Act shall become effective upon its approval by the Governor or upon its becoming law
54 without such approval and shall apply to any vacancy occurring on or after the effective date
55 of this Act.
56 SECTION 3.
57 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
